                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Bangalore, Sept. 13 (PTI): Four tigers have died, three of them of old age, in the past four days in Bannerghatta National Park on the outskirts of the city, a senior forest official said today.           
	The tigers named King, 21, Lakshman, 18, and Shankar, 24, and a three-and-a-half-year-old cub Divya have died in the park in the last four days, additional principal chief conservator of forests N.N. Jayakumar said.           
	While Shankar, King and Lakshman died because of old age, Divya died of diarrhoea for which she was being treated for the last 12 days, he said.                   
	 Indore (PTI): A 25-year-old student of Indian Institute of Management, drowned in the Sitlamata Falls here, police said. Vinod Verma, a second-year post graduate student went there picnicking on Sunday evening and stepped into the falls for a swim.                   
	 Mumbai (PTI): Actress Kajol gave birth to her second child, a boy, on Monday. Nysa, Kajols elder child with Ajay Devgn is seven years old. The actress delivered the baby around 9.20 am at the Lilavati Hospital here. Sources close to the couple said the mother and the baby were doing fine.                  
	 Hyderabad (PTI): The CBI completed on Monday arguments on the charges to be framed in the Rs 14,000-crore Satyam Computers scam. It sought to frame charges against each of the 10 accused and presented before the court supporting documents.                   
	Ghaziabad (PTI): A criminal case has been registered against a gynaecologist in Uttar Pradesh for attempting to conduct an abortion on a minor girl raped by her landlord, police said.                  
	 Thiruvananthapuram (PTI): A former Lok Sabha member, K.S. Manoj, who quit the CPM last year protesting the partys approach towards religion, has joined the Congress.                                                                                                                                              
